                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Great is our Lord, and mighty in power; His understanding is infinite. The Lord lifts up the humble.”
                                                                            <b>Psalms 147:5-6a NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“And there is no creature hidden from His sight, but all things are naked and open to the eyes of Him to whom we must give account.”
                                                                            <b>Hebrews 4:13 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Omniscience means all knowledge.  Our God is aware of all dimensions of this universe and all it contains.  He knows the number of hairs on our heads.  Before a word is formed on our lips, He knows it altogether. All things were always, and always will be known to Him, there is no future, no past because to God all things are present.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10"><b>Psalm 147:5-6a</b> confirms God’s omnipotence and omnipresence, while addressing His omniscience. He is all powerful, His knowledge is limitless, total and all embracing.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Over the years I have learned when in full blown panic to pause.  A hard lesson to learn yes, but once achieved there are great rewards.  I’ve come to realize that whatever and I mean whatever circumstance I’m experiencing God knew it was going to take place.  He was not surprised.  One thing I know I/we must learn is to do is to take God at His word as stated in <b>Isaiah 1:1a</b>,
                                                                            “Come now, and let us reason together”, says the Lord. This is so much more than prayer.  It is entering His presence understanding that He knows, and not having to explain the situation to Him.  It is allowing ourselves to be yielded enough and assured we can question the circumstance without timidity seeking the direction we need knowing He holds the perfect answer and will guide us through the pain, sorrow and heartache we are experiencing.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">The all powerful, all knowing God who is limitless lifts up the humble.  Sometimes we think we need many words when actually we need none.  He already knows.  Whatever the circumstance is it is okay to sit before our Father and be still, let tears fall and to listen for His still small voice .
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Do you really believe today that there isn’t anything that the all powerful, all knowing, ever present, limitless God won’t walk with you through?
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10"><b>ABBA Father</b> today we come asking we become diligent is seeking Your truths.  We pray we make our relationship with You our highest priority.  To know You more in who you really are.  Help us to set aside our untrue or man made perception of who You are and grow in truth of the all knowing, ever present, all powerful God that You are.  We love you Lord ...we do.
                                                                        </p>
